    <briefdescription>
<para>Configuration used to format ext2 file system. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>If a field is set to 0 then default value is used. (In volume name the first cell of an array must be 0 to use default value.)</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>block_size</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Requested size of block. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fs_size</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Requested size of file system. If 0 then whole available memory is used. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>bytes_per_inode</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Requested memory for one inode. It is used to calculate number of inodes in created file system. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>uuid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>UUID for created file system. Used when set_uuid is true. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>volume_name</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Name for created file system. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>set_uuid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If true then UUID from that structure is used in created file system. If false then UUID (ver4) is generated. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
